<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7316> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7316" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pr.? 67? On his name and identity, see Shackleton Bailey, CLA 1.292, on Att. 1.1.2. Against Münzer (RE), he favors Drumann's view that while he was a candidate he was adopted by a Marcius Figulus and is the C. Marcius C. f. Figulus who became consul in 64 (see Marcius, RE no.63, above). This would explain the notice Caesare et Turmo in the Chronographer of 354. See also E. W. Gray, Antichthon 13, 1979, 56-65." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4684> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4684" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A candidate for the consulship of 64 (Cic. Att. 1.1.2; cf. Flacc. 98, on his name)." .
